observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Local Chief Executive require the GAD Focal point System to:
(a) continue its efforts to improve gender mainstreaming to achieve full compliance with the provisions of relevant laws and regulations;
(b) inform/ submit the revised GPB to the DILG and the Audit Team should there be any update/ changes in the original GPB;
(c) improve the reporting functions and ensure that GAD internal data are consistent and corroborative by checking the accuracy of the amounts in order to be useful to the users;
(d) direct all members of the GAD Focal Point System to conduct a gender analysis of the City’s program, project and activities through the administration of HGDG for purposes of GAD budget attribution; and
(e) create a multi-year GAD Agenda as basis for the annual GPB by using the templates provided in PCW Memorandum Circular No. 2018-04 dated September 19, 2018; and
(f) timely submit to the Audit Team the GAD Accomplishment Report in compliance with COA Circular No. 2014-001.

We recommended that the LCE direct the City Accountant to:

ensure that liabilities shall only be recognized in the books founded on existing obligations at the reporting date duly supported with approved contracts/POs and other valid documents;      
revert to the unappropriated surplus all unpaid obligations without available valid and legally approved documents;

submit all of the documents necessary to support the propriety, validity and existence of the Accounts Payable and Other Payable accounts of Ᵽ41,792,965.28 and Ᵽ3,604,144.53, respectively, as of December 31, 2020 for verification;

recognize the collections on sale of bid documents and retention moneys to Trust Liability and Guaranty/Security Deposit Payable accounts;

investigate and effect the necessary correcting entries on the erroneous recording and/or excess payments BAC honoraria of Ᵽ81,000.00, Palayan City Employees Multi-Purpose Cooperative of Ᵽ61,606.93, RG Automotive Body Repair Ᵽ100,000, DSWD Region III of Ᵽ200.00 and retention money from Other Payable account to appropriate accounts; 

send/issue demand letters to concerned payees/accountable officials and employees to impose refund of the excess payments for BAC honoraria, Palayan City Employees Multi-Purpose Cooperative, RG Automotive Body Repair and DSWD Region III; and 

use and maintain duly accomplished prescribed SL for all Accounts and Other Payable.

observations.managementAction:
