observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the LCE direct (a) the concerned SDOs to (i) submit satisfactory explanation why the cash assistance in the amount of P303,000.00 which were not signed by the payees were included in the liquidation documents and why the payroll amount exceeded that of her cash advance; and 

(ii) maintain cashbook for cash advances; and 


(b) the Accountant to (i) make adjusting entries corresponding to the amount of unsigned payrolls; 




(ii) accept only payrolls with signatures of payees as support of the LR; 




(iii) investigate and effect necessary correcting/adjusting entry on payouts that exceeded the cash advance drawn by the SDO; 


(iv) exert all effort to send demand letters to concerned officials and employees with unliquidated cash advances; and 



(v) require the concerned officers and employees to settle/liquidate their cash advances immediately upon serving its purpose and submit valid documents to support the liquidation.

We recommended that the LCE direct the 

(a) City Treasurer (i) to limit the PCF to the amount authorized in SP Resolution No. 14-A Series of 2016;  



(b) City Accountant to ensure that Driver’s Trip Tickets are properly accomplished and serially numbered;  



(c) Concerned official to issue individual Driver’s Trip Ticket for each travel and avoid including places not within the route of destination;  




(d) Drivers and GSO Officer to submit Monthly Report of Official Travel and Monthly Report of Fuel Consumption of Government Motor Transportation, respectively;



(e) PCF Custodian to ensure that payments out of the fund are properly and completely supported with the required documents; and 




(f) concerned officials to return/refund the excess fuel claimed.

